  "prompt": "What is the salary of an RTO officer?",
  "response": "The salary of an RTO (Regional Transport Officer) can vary based on several factors such as location, experience, and the specific government or state regulations governing such positions. In India, for example, the salary for an RTO officer may typically range from approximately \u20b930,000 to \u20b970,000 per month at the entry level, depending on the state government pay scales. \n\nAdditionally, RTO officers may receive various allowances and benefits, including health benefits, retirement benefits, and other perks. For the most accurate and updated salary information, it is advisable to consult specific government job postings or official state transport department websites.",
